text: Start of school update

post_text:
Here’s a quick follow-up on the start of school August 31st. The answer today is yes face-to-face instruction!
A survey has been sent and many are responding. This survey will be available until August 1st.

This data will be used during the Start Well committee on August 3rd. The committee is made up of staff, parents, and school board member.
The committee will develop recommendations for the school board to consider on August 12th.
Procedural information for the start of school will be sent home to families shortly after the 12th.

Currently, I anticipate the committee will suggest that we start school as normal as possible with some optional precautions to recommend.

Dan Baldwin, Superintendent
Walls Schools #51-5
text:

post_text:
Here are a few announcements concerning school activities:
1. Kindergarten Screening is scheduled for August 5, 2020. If you have a child who will be 5-years old on September 1, 2020, he/she is eligible to start kindergarten. If you know of a child living in the Wall School District who fits that category, please inform the parents/guardians. We need names and addresses so information can be sent.
2. The first day of school for the students is August 31, 2020. School will be dismissed at 2:00PM that day. We will not have school on September 7, 2020 but we will have school on September 11, 2020. The school calendar can be found at, https://wall.k12.sd.us/Files/Days-In-Service.pdf.
3. We are setting up a committee to discuss the start of school. The first meeting is scheduled for August 3, 2020.

****PLEASE SHARE*****

The Wall Eagles will be joining other area schools in "Be the Light" campaign.

Tomorrow, Thursday evening, April 16, 2020, we will be turning on our football field lights at 8:20 for 20 minutes. We are doing this in honor of those who work in the medical field, our seniors and all the participants in extra-curricular activities that have been cancelled.

Please come and drive by the Wall Athletic Complex during this time and honk to show your support.

PLEASE REMEMBER TO ADHERE TO SOCIAL DISTANCING PROTOCOL AND STAY IN YOUR VEHICLES!.

Why the exact time?
20:20 is military time for 8:20 and the lights will stay on for 20 minutes to honor the class of 2020. #GOEAGLES

post_text:
Mr. Heathershaw has been organizing events to kick off Heart Month in February. We hosted Red Out at the doubleheader on Friday against Kadoka, along with the Eagle Challenges and awareness messages last week. Thank you to our students and the Wall community for their support of the Red Out which raised $448 for the American Heart Association in Western South Dakota.

These donations help fund community initiatives, education, research and quality of care – all to fight the number one killer in the world – heart disease.

post_text:
The Wall Angel Tree Program is a non-profit organization. The goal is to provide Christmas gifts for children in our community that might not otherwise have gifts on Christmas. This year ornaments were hung on the tree at First Interstate Bank on Monday, November 25, 2019. If you are interested in giving please choose an ornament from the tree, fulfill the child's wish, then return the unwrapped gifts to the bank by Monday, December 16th (we just extended the deadline). The committee will prepare and wrap the gifts and fill a special stocking for the child. A donation box will also be available at First Interstate Bank if you would prefer to make a monetary donation.

There are still approximately 30 ornaments on the tree!

Thanks!
Kelli Sundall
Wall School Counselor

post_text:
From Superintendent Dan Baldwin:
Good morning Wall School District,
At 10:14 this morning the Wall School Building went into a level one secure the building status. This means that class went on as normal, but no one was allowed to enter or leave the building. This was due to a nearby law enforcement pursuit off campus on the interstate. The pursuit has ended an all-clear was given at approx. 10:31 and all classes are now back to normal.
The secured state was lifted after law enforcement was confident there was no longer a safety concern. The safety of our staff and students is our utmost priority as this was done to ensure that safety. There is no active safety concern and the school has resumed normal operations.

post_text: This is going to be an amazing event, please make plans to attend.
shared_text:
Wall Eagle Athletics
August 13, 2019 at 8:06 AM ·

Mark your calendars for September 8th! Thanks to the Wall Area Booster Club, we are able to bring in Rob Miller from Proactive Coaching to our school! Proactive coaching is an organization that teaches coaches, teachers, athletes and parents how to make a positive impact on young people’s lives through sport. They hold character and integrity high for all coaches, athletes and parents to display. Rob is an outstanding speaker and this is an amazing opportunity for our community.

Everyone is welcome to attend, whether you have a student in school or not! From experience, you won’t want to miss this speaker!

Sunday, September 8th at 3:00pm will be the coaches presentation.

4:30 will be the athletes presentation (all ages)

6:00 will be the parents/community talk

Please make plans to attend and check out their Facebook page for more information on what they do.

Here is some good information on summer feeding programs throughout South Dakota. You can text, call or check out the Summer Food Service Program on the USDA web page.

How to Participate:
Finding an SFSP Site
Are you a parent or guardian looking for SFSP sites near you? Find a summer site in your community with our Summer Meal Site Finder mapping tool. You can also text “Summer Meals” to 97779 or call 1-866-348-6479 to find a site near you.

post_text: Congratulations to our Jr High Rodeo athletes!
shared_text:
Anita-Mike Heathershaw
May 19, 2019 at 5:22 PM ·

The Wall Jr High kids that will be competing in the National Junior High Rodeo Finals in Huron SD in June. Jonnie Jo Anders and Piper Cordes will be representing SD in Pole Bending-both with #4 split position on the team. T Merrill will be representing SD in the Team Roping in the #2 position on the team, #3 position in the Barrel Racing on the team, #4 position on the team in the Ribbon Roping and the Girls Goat Tying. Kipp Cordes will be representing SD in Boys Breakaway Roping with a #3 position on the team. Matthew Heathershaw will be representing SD in Boys Tie Down Roping & Ribbon Roping with the #2 position on the team in both. Also a #3 position on the team in Steer Saddle Bronc Riding. Good Luck to this great bunch of Cowgirls & Cowboys!!
